=== Reception ===

The soundtrack received positive reviews with many critics praising the amalgam of Bengali with Hindi lyrics used in the songs. [[CNN-IBN]] mentioned, "''Aami Shotti Bolchi'' not only has interesting lyrics but also conveys the feel of Kolkata. The song is successful even if it expresses about only 20 percent of the local feel of Kolkata. ''Kahaani'' may not be a collector's item but it features right voices as per the overall mood of the album. ''Aami Shotti Bolchi'' and ''Ekla Cholo Re'' have the potential to fetch your attention."<ref>{{cite news|last=Vats|first=Rohit|title=Music review: 'Kahaani' focuses on nostalgia|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/music-review-kahaani-focuses-on-nostalgia/232715-45-76.html|accessdate=30 March 2012|publisher=IBNLive|date=24 February 2012 }}</ref> ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'' rated the album with 3 stars out of 5 concluding that, "Good music certainly has its way of standing out among the ordinary."<ref>{{cite news|title=Kahaani music review|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-29/music-reviews/31110240_1_vishal-shekhar-special-appearance-guitars|accessdate=15 May 2012|newspaper=The Times of India|date=29 February 2012|author=[[Mumbai Mirror]]}}</ref> Reviewing the soundtrack, Anand Vaishnav for [[India Times]] commented that, "''Kahaani'' as an album, stays honest to the theme of the film."<ref>{{cite news|last=Vaishnav|first=Anand|title=Music Review&nbsp;<U+2014> Kahaani|url=http://www.indiatimes.com/bollywood/music-review-kahaani-12663.html|accessdate=15 May 2012|newspaper=[[India Times]]|date=15 February 2012}}</ref>

== Marketing ==
''Kahaani's'' first look poster was launched on 2 December 2011,<ref>{{cite news|title=First Look: Vidya Balan in Kahaani|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/FIRST-LOOK-Vidya-Balan-in-Kahaani/Article1-776399.aspx|accessdate=4 May 2012|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=2 December 2011}}</ref> while the official trailer was launched on 5 January 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=First look of Vidya Balan's Kahaani launched|url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/first-look-of-vidya-balans-i-kahaani-i-launched/220329?sp|accessdate=4 May 2012|publisher=NDTV|date=5 January 2012}}</ref> The first look poster, portraying a pregnant Vidya Balan as the lead protagonist and with no romantic element, received a warm response from the public who expected it to be just a good film that might do a moderate business at the best. The critics also set their expectations low owing to the director's last two box office failures.<ref name="ibn rathnam 28march" />

=== Promotions ===
''Kahaani'' was extensively promoted in various cities across the country. Balan appeared in public with a prosthetic pregnant belly during promotional events of the film. She mingled with people in various public places, including railway stations, bus stands and [[Brihanmumbai Electric Supply and Transport|BEST]] buses in Mumbai,<ref name=ZNpromotion>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/vidya-s-arnab-bagchi-found_107140.htm|title=Vidya's Arnab Bagchi found!|date=6 March 2012|accessdate=26 March 2012|publisher=Zee News}}</ref> and shopping malls in [[Ahmedabad]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Trivedi|first=Tanvi|title=Vidya Balan to promote 'Kahaani' in Ahmedabad|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-05/news-interviews/31123542_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-pregnant-woman|accessdate=9 April 2012|newspaper=The Times of India|date=5 Mar 2012|agency=TNN}}</ref> Along with a baby bump, she often carried a sketch of her missing husband; showing it to people and asking for their help in finding him.<ref name=ZNpromotion/> Besides, the film was promoted in Kolkata at several shopping malls and a metro station.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-publicity-zara-hatke-2983254.html|title=Publicity zara hatke!|last=Risbood|first=Vaibhavi|newspaper=[[Daily Bhaskar]]|date=16 March 202|accessdate=26 March 2012}}</ref> On 3 March 2012, Balan, along with the director Ghosh and co-star Parambrata, urged the crowd at the [[Tollygunge]] Metro station to watch the film. She also presented gift hampers to the five top customers of the designer store, Jhoomar, at Allenby Road, as part of the Free Spirited Woman program launched by the store. The response to the campaign was overwhelming as residents from the neighboring houses peeped out of their windows to capture Balan on their cameras while school and college students waited outside with their notebooks for a glimpse of her. Later on the same day, Balan distributed ''Kahaani's'' music CDs, t-shirts and a leaflet with Arnab Bagchi's photograph at the Avani Riverside Mall in [[Howrah]] and requested the public to watch the film stating that its a story of Kolkata and had been shot on the streets of the city.<ref name="Vidya Story @ TT">{{cite news|title=Vidya's story|url=http://vv.telegraphindia.com/1120305/jsp/entertainment/story_15211741.jsp|accessdate=22 May 2012|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=5 March 2012}}</ref>

On 8 March 2012, Balan appeared on Indian channel [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors']] daily soap ''[[Uttaran]]'' to promote the film. On the show, Balan dressed as her character Vidya Bagchi was seen sticking posters of her husband Arnab Bagchi as part of her relentless search for her missing husband and then interacting with the female lead of the show.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/Vidya-Balan-identifies-with-tv-actors-dilemma/articleshow/12083893.cms/|title=Vidya Balan identifies with tv actors dilemma|last=Vyavahare|first=Renuka|newspaper=The Times of India|date=21 March 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012|agency=TNN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tina's 'Uttaran' tales with Vidya's 'Kahaani'|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/idiotbox/tina-s-uttaran-tales-with-vidya-s-kahaani_106430.htm|accessdate=21 March 2012|publisher=Zee News|agency=IANS|date=23 February 2012}}</ref> The identity of the actor who played the role of Arnab Bagchi, was also not revealed to keep the mystery element alive.<ref name=ZNpromotion/>

=== Online game ===
As per the marketing strategy, the film was associated with [[Ibibo|Ibibo.com]] to develop an online based game on their social networking website. The game ''The Great Indian Parking Wars'', required the gamers to park Vidya's taxi on a friend's street to help her in the journey to find her missing husband. Gamers also got in touch with Balan through her gaming profile on the website and won movie merchandise and tickets. The game was a hit among online gamers reaching about 50,000 hits within the first 10 days of its launch.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan's 'Kahaani' hit among online gamers|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/vidya-balan-s-kahaani-hit-among-online-gamers_107968.htm|accessdate=21 March 2012|publisher=Zee News|date=20 March 2012|agency=IANS}}</ref>

== Release ==

''Kahaani'', being a woman's film, was released on 9 March 2012, a day after the [[International Women's Day]]<ref name=Motherhood@ZN>{{cite news|title=Vidya's 'Kahaani': a celebration of womanhood|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/vidya-s-kahaani-a-celebration-of-womanhood_107271.htm|accessdate=2 April 2012|publisher=Zee News|date=8 March 2012}}</ref> in 1100 screens worldwide.<ref name=75crore@IBN /> After starring in ''[[Ishqiya]]'' (2010), ''[[No One Killed Jessica]]'' (2011) and ''[[The Dirty Picture]]'' (2011), ''Kahaani'' was Balan's fourth [[woman's film|woman centric film]]<ref name=VidyaStrikeGold@ZN>{{cite news|title=Will Vidya stike gold again with 'Kahaani'?|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/will-vidya-stike-gold-again-with-kahaani_107075.htm|accessdate=28 March 2012|publisher=Zee News|date=5 March 2012|agency=IANS}}</ref> to win her widespread praise and coverage for her non-conventional approach in portraying strong female-oriented roles.<ref name="Kahaani Rave Reviews">{{cite web|title=Kahaani receives rave reviews from film critics|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/2012/kahaani-rave-reviews-critics-verdict-110312.html|accessdate=11 March 2012|work=oneindia.in}}</ref><ref name=firstlook>{{cite news|title=First look: Vidya Balan in Kahaani|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/FIRST-LOOK-Vidya-Balan-in-Kahaani/Article1-776399.aspx|accessdate=1 December 2011|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=1 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=No ordinary Kahaani|url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/component/content/article/346-show-time/48714-no-ordinary-kahaani.html|first=Meenakshi|last=Rao|date=10 March 2012|accessdate=6 April 2012|newspaper=[[The Pioneer (Indian newspaper)|The Pioneer]]}}</ref> Shilpa Rathnam from [[CNN-IBN]] stated that, "Though ''Kahaani'' was ready before ''The Dirty Picture'', the move to release Vidya's Silk avatar first paid off. A sexy siren after the pregnant Vidya may have backfired. Also the unconventional ''Kahaani'' was pushed by Vidya's popularity post ''The Dirty Picture'', the National Award for Best Actress included."<ref name="ibn rathnam 28march">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kahaani-the-mother-of-a-success-story/243546-8-66.html|title=Kahaani: The mother of a success story|last=Rathnam|first=Shilpa|date=28 March 2012|accessdate=28 March 2012|publisher=IBNLive}}</ref>

=== Controversy ===

On 5 March 2012, the [[Kolkata Metro]] Railway authorities objected to a scene from the film where Balan waits on the platform to board a Metro train at the [[Kalighat]] station and is pushed perilously by a man standing next to her onto the tracks, as soon as the train arrives. The railway officials requested the film's producer to remove the scene from the promos and the film, as it would remind people of the past acts of suicides on the tracks which tarnished the image of India's first tube railway. In the past, a total of 224 cases were registered for suicides of which 124 resulted in death.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kahaani's dream, Kolkata Metro's nightmare|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/kahaani-s-dream-kolkata-metro-s-nightmare_107035.htm|publisher=Zee News|agency=IANS|date=5 March 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012}}</ref> Following a discussion with the Metro authorities, the filmmakers submitted a video of the entire controversial scene to the authorities and explained to them of not including anything in the film that tarnished the image of the Metro railway or prompted people to commit suicide on the tracks. The railway officials were convinced and withdrew their objections and the scene which was shot using computer-generated imagery, was retained in the film but was however removed from the promos.<ref>{{cite news|title=Metro clears Vidya's scene in 'Kahaani'|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/metro-clears-vidya-s-scene-in-kahaani_107083.htm|publisher=Zee News|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=5 March 2012|agency=PTI}}</ref>

=== Social screening ===

A special screening of the film was organized on 16 March 2012 in [[Bengaluru]] by [[Cinepolis#International|Cinepolis]] for the women of an NGO [[SOS Children's Villages]] that supports children and women from underprivileged families. More than 40 women attended the screening and, according to the director of the NGO, "... cherished the movie and their time at the cinema. I am certain that this initiative will encourage many more organizations to come forward and show their support for our cause."<ref>{{cite news|title=Screening of 'Kahaani' for underprivileged women|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/screening-of-kahaani-for-underprivileged-women_107717.htm|publisher=Zee News|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=16 March 2012|agency=IANS}}</ref>

=== Television and home media ===
''Kahaani's'' satellite rights were acquired by [[STAR TV]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Star TV acquires 'Kahaani', 'Housefull 2<U+2032> & others|url=http://www.media247.co.uk/atlantic/star-tv-acquires-kahaani-housefull-2-others|publisher=Media 247|accessdate=6 June 2012|work=Biz Asia Atlantic|first=Lakh|last=Baddhan|date=5 April 2012}}</ref> for a price of {{INRConvert|8|c}},<ref name="TV Rights @ Youtube">{{cite video|year=2012|month=March|title=Kahaani's TV Rights Sold for 8 Crore|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pcmM4TCnEX4|type=Television production|time=0:52|publisher=ZingTV|accessdate=6 June 2012 }}</ref> which was supposedly the highest ever price paid for a female centric film.<ref name="TV Rights @ Youtube" /> The Indian television premiere of the film took place on [[STAR (India)|Star India's]] movie channel [[Movies OK]]<ref name="Movies OK @ BS">{{cite news|title=STAR expands Ok brand with a new movie channel|url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/star-expands-ok-branda-new-movie-channel/473629/|newspaper=[[Business Standard]]|accessdate=7 June 2012|date=7 May 2012}}</ref> on 3 June 2012.<ref name="Movies OK @ MSN">{{cite web|title=Movies OK to dazzle viewers|url=http://entertainment.in.msn.com/tv/movies-ok-to-dazzle-viewers|publisher=MSN India|accessdate=7 June 2012|date=29 May 2012}}</ref>

The [[DVD]] of the film was released on 17 May 2012<ref name="DVD launch @ Youtube">{{cite video|year=2012|month=May|title=Vidya Balan at 'Kahaani DVD' launch|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4KDYwcnv4ho|type=Television production|time=1:55|publisher=|accessdate=22 May 2012 }}</ref> across all regions in one-disc pack complying the NTSC format. The DVD's of the film are manufactured by [[Shemaroo Entertainment]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani (DVD)|url=http://www.greatdealworld.com/kahaani--p-3368.html|publisher=Great Deal World|accessdate=22 May 2012|work=Shemaroo}}</ref> and contained additional content such as the 'Making of the Film', 'The Success Party' and 'Promotional Songs'.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani DVD (2012)|url=http://www.onlineindianmart.com/hindi-movies-thriller-c-1_10/kahaani-dvd-2012-p-7502|publisher=Online Indian Mart|accessdate=22 May 2012|work=Shemaroo}}</ref> The [[VCD]] and [[Blu-Ray]] versions were also released simultaneously.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani (VCD)|url=http://www.greatdealworld.com/kahaani--p-3369.html|publisher=Great Deal World|accessdate=22 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani (Blu-Ray)|url=http://www.greatdealworld.com/kahaani--p-3370.html|publisher=Great Deal World|accessdate=22 May 2012|work=Shemaroo}}</ref>

== Reception ==
''Kahaani'' garnered mostly positive reviews from critics. According to review aggregators BollyMovieReviewz and ReviewGang the film received a rating of 3.71 out of 5<ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani review|url=http://bollymoviereviewz.blogspot.in/2012/03/kahaani-movie-review-rajeev-taran.html|accessdate=24 March 2012|date=11 March 2012|publisher=BollyMovieReviewz}}{{Rating|3.71|5}}</ref> and 8 out of 10<ref>{{cite web|title=Kahaani movie review|url=http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/225-Kahaani-Review|publisher=Review Gang|accessdate=9 March 2012}}{{Rating|8|10}}</ref> respectively, based on the reviews given by professional critics. The film is termed as one of the rare Hindi films to receive an average rating of just under 5 stars from critics. Good word of mouth publicity played a major part in its popularity besides the rave reviews.<ref name="ibn rathnam 28march"/> [[IMDB]] included the film in their list of ''The Top 50 Thrillers of all time'' making it the only Indian film to be featured in the list, ranking at 12.<ref name="ibn rathnam 28march" />

